---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us" description="Learn more about US Visa Tracker and our mission to provide accurate, accessible immigration processing data.">
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-8">About Us</h1>
		<div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none text-neutral-600">
			<p class="text-xl">Our mission is simple: to bring transparency and clarity to the complex, often frustrating US immigration process.</p>
			
			<h2>Why We Built This</h2>
			<p>Applying for a US visa, adjusting status to permanent residency, or seeking citizenship involves navigating a labyrinth of forms, wait times, and policy shifts. When we realized that thousands of applicants spend hours each day anxiously checking disjointed government portals, we knew there had to be a better way.</p>
			
			<h2>Our Approach</h2>
			<p>We source all our data strictly from official public endpoints provided by the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) and the Department of State. We then process, aggregate, and visualize this data to give you a clear understanding of current wait times and historical trends.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>No Paywalls:</strong> Essential immigration data should be free.</li>
				<li><strong>Privacy First:</strong> We don't ask for your personal receipt numbers.</li>
				<li><strong>Unbiased Insights:</strong> We rely strictly on data, not hearsay.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Disclaimer</h2>
			<p>We are a team of data enthusiasts and technologists, not immigration lawyers. US Visa Tracker is an independent platform and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or representative of USCIS, the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), the Department of State, or any other government entity.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
